name: Licensure by endorsement
text: [§448B-6]  Licensure by endorsement.  The director shall grant, upon application and payment of proper fees, licensure to a person who, at the time of application, holds a valid certification or license as a dietitian issued by another state, territory, or jurisdiction if the requirements for that certification or license are equal to, or greater than, the requirements of this chapter. [L 2000, c 280, pt of §2]
